				I am lvl 9 hie wizard and i think that begging and twinking and all that is ok, the reason is that newbie players that have just got the game aren't as skilled as some of the other people out there, especially the high levels. What im trying to say is that i think that high level people shouldn't be so fricken stuck up, sure they want someone to enjoy the game, but how can they when they are constantly getting killed cause they cant raise enough pp to get some decent armor, or (as i have been through)casters have a hard enough time getting enough money to buy new spells, and such. What i think is that high level people should at least help a newbie out by giving him/her 5 pp out of their 5000 pp stash, or giving some unwanted armor that'll help them more than theirselves. I was lucky enough to meet a very nice high level person when i was lvl 1 that gave me 20 PP! just for taking him to a local merchant. 20 pp may not sound like much to all you high level people out there but to a newbie, its like they just won 1 million dollars. If someone ever wants me to go buy them 3 pp worth of armor because they cant afford it yet, i would be more than happy to, just out of genoriosity. And what really makes me sick is the act that a lvl 1 newbie will go up to a lvl 60 vet, asking for 1 PP! and he will say &quot;nope&quot;, i mean come on! Well ive gone on and on, but i hope that someone out there will be kind enough in the future to do what is right. <br> P.S. What i mean by begging is like asking once for something, people who think that they deserve stuff, or keep asking should be slapped! <br>                                            Aragornz                                 Sollusk Ro server                                          Wizard on the 9th saeson 		

