		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				The whole point of the game is to adventure and accomplish things, like finding new armor or enough money to buy new armor. When someone just gives you a ton of stuff early on, you miss out on the fun of the early levels. <br>  <br> There's nothing wrong with twinking or someone giving you some cash, etc., but if you're doing this a LOT you should ask yourself why you're playing the game. <br>  <br> Let's say for example, someone passes down an awesome weapon and throws on some uber buffs etc. to help. Hopped up the player runs around and gains levels in no time. Those levels and items just don't mean as much as the ordinary player's. <br>  <br> If you spend the time to work for what you have, then you will understand why others aren't eager to help out beggars or overly-twink other players. <br>  <br> Don't get me wrong, a minor twink isn't that bad. Perhaps a decent weapon or one or two pieces of armor... The bottom line is, lower level players don't NEED awesome equipment because they aren't fighting awesome monsters.		

